701202f-b.text:
2226-2232 Gunther Ave., east side, between Stillwell and Astor Aves., showing a 2-family dwelling in the residential district known as Pelham Parkway Gardens. The numbers 16 and 17, on the door fronts, refer to the lot numbers on which the two sections of the dwelling are located; the picture having been taken before the house was sold.
About 1923.
Kenneth Clark.
701202f-b.folder: Gunther Avenue & Stillwell Avenue, Bronx, NY

Stillwell Ave. (right), north side, east from Gunther to Wickhaw Aves., showing new homes in the residential development known as Pelham Parkway Gardens. Also shown (left) is the east side of Gunther Ave., north from Stillwell to Astor Aves.

701868f-a.text:
Stillwell Ave. (right), north side, east from Gunther to Wickham Aves. Also shown is the east side of Gunther Ave., north from Stillwell, to but not including Astor Ave. These dwellings are part of the new residential district known as Pelham Parkway Gardens.
About 1923.
